    <!-- ============================================================
         SECTION 3: THE CHALLENGE (DARK)
         ============================================================ -->
    <section id="challenge" data-theme="dark" aria-labelledby="challenge-heading" class="section" style="background:var(--color-secondary);color:var(--color-secondary-foreground);">
      <div class="container">
        <!-- Header -->
        <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-primary-400);">THE STATUS QUO</p>
        <h2 id="challenge-heading" class="text-display-md" style="color:#f7f8f8;margin-top:12px;">What Schools Currently Rely On</h2>
        <p class="text-body-lg" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);max-width:65ch;margin-top:16px;">Teachers assemble spreadsheets. Permission slips serve as the only documentation. Risk assessment means checking the weather forecast the morning of departure.</p>

        <!-- Pain Cards -->
        <div class="grid gap-8" style="margin-top:48px;grid-template-columns:1fr;" id="pain-grid">
          <!-- Pain Card 1: Staff Time -->
          <div class="dark-surface" style="border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:24px;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-400)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/>
            </svg>
            <div class="text-display-md" style="color:#f7f8f8;margin-top:16px;font-weight:700;" aria-label="$700 to $1,400 in staff hours per field trip">$700 - $1,400</div>
            <p class="text-eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:4px;">in staff hours per trip</p>
            <p class="text-body-md" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:16px;">Every field trip requires 15-30 hours of manual safety planning by teachers who are not risk professionals.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Pain Card 2: Liability Exposure -->
          <div class="dark-surface" style="border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:24px;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-label="Warning">
              <path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/>
            </svg>
            <div class="text-display-md" style="color:#f7f8f8;margin-top:16px;font-weight:700;" aria-label="$500,000 to $2 million average settlement for trip-related incidents">$500K - $2M</div>
            <p class="text-eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:4px;">average settlement for trip-related incidents</p>
            <p class="text-body-md" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:16px;">When a student is injured on a trip, &ldquo;What precautions did the district take?&rdquo; is the first question asked.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Pain Card 3: Documentation Gap -->
          <div class="dark-surface" style="border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:24px;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-400)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M14.5 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V7.5L14.5 2z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="9.5" y1="12.5" x2="14.5" y2="17.5"/><line x1="14.5" y1="12.5" x2="9.5" y2="17.5"/>
            </svg>
            <div class="text-display-md" style="color:#f7f8f8;margin-top:16px;font-weight:700;" aria-label="Zero formal risk documentation">Zero</div>
            <p class="text-eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:4px;">formal risk documentation</p>
            <p class="text-body-md" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:16px;">Permission slips are not safety plans. A signed waiver is not evidence of due diligence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Liability Comparison -->
        <div class="dark-surface" style="border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:32px;margin-top:48px;" role="group" aria-label="Board liability comparison: without versus with SafeTrekr">
          <h3 class="text-heading-sm" style="color:#f7f8f8;margin-bottom:24px;">The Board Liability Question</h3>
          <div class="grid gap-8" style="grid-template-columns:1fr;" id="liability-grid">
            <!-- Without -->
            <div>
              <p class="text-eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-destructive);letter-spacing:0.08em;">WITHOUT SAFETREKR</p>
              <p class="text-body-lg" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);font-style:italic;margin-top:12px;">&ldquo;What documentation did the district have before approving this trip?&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="text-body-md" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:16px;">Answer: Permission slips. A teacher&rsquo;s spreadsheet. Verbal assurances.</p>
            </div>
            <!-- With -->
            <div>
              <p class="text-eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-primary-400);letter-spacing:0.08em;">WITH SAFETREKR</p>
              <p class="text-body-lg" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);font-style:italic;margin-top:12px;">&ldquo;Here is the 17-section safety review conducted by a professional analyst, the government intelligence risk score, and the complete evidence binder with SHA-256 verification.&rdquo;</p>
              <p class="text-body-md" style="color:var(--color-secondary-muted);margin-top:16px;">Answer: A documented, tamper-evident record of every precaution the district took.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

